    "Let K, a, and Λ a be as in the discussion before Lemma 5.9.",
    "Then we have ℓ∈Λa µ(T (ℓ) a) = ∞.",
    "The Borel-Cantelli lemma [FriJ23, Lemma 21.3.5] in probability theory shows that, for almost all σ ∈ G K, there exist infinitely many prime numbers ℓ ∈ Λ a such that σ ∈ T (ℓ) a.",
    "Lemma 2.5 implies that the torsion-free Z-module G m (K(σ))/G m (K(σ)) tor is not free for almost all σ ∈ G K.",
